org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.impl

Class DefaultCredentialStorePluginImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.impl.DefaultCredentialStorePluginImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.CredentialStorePlugin, org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.ExecContextPlugin

    public class DefaultCredentialStorePluginImpl
extends Object
implements org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.CredentialStorePlugin
    This default implementation of CredentialStorePlugin uses CredentialStore to manage credentials.

    The MASTER_KEY_FILE initialization property specifies the Path of the master key file.

    If the CREDENTIAL_FILE initialization property is defined, it specifies the Path of the credential file. The default credential file is credentials.properties in the workspace metadata directory.

    This mappings between resource Pattern's and corresponding realms and users are defined using runtime properties defined on the root ClassificationNode:

    • RESOURCE_PATTERN_REALM_USER_MAPPINGS: ","-separated list of resource-realm-user mapping names. For each such name, a CredentialStore.ResourcePatternRealmUser is created.
    • RESOURCE_PATTERN_REALM_USER_MAPPING_RESOURCE_PATTERN.<name>: Literal value of CredentialStore.ResourcePatternRealmUser.patternResource.
    • RESOURCE_PATTERN_REALM_USER_MAPPING_REALM.<name>: Value of CredentialStore.ResourcePatternRealmUser.realm.
    • RESOURCE_PATTERN_REALM_USER_MAPPING_USER.<name>: Value of CredentialStore.ResourcePatternRealmUser.user.
    If UserInteractionCallbackPlugin.isBatchMode() returns false, this class interacts with the user when appropriate to obtain missing passwords, as recommended in CredentialStorePlugin.

    In addition to implementing CredentialStorePlugin, this class publicly provides access to the CredentialStore instance allowing to obtain information about realms and explicitly modify the passwords, operations which are not supported by the interface. This is meant to be used by a tool that would assume this specific implementation of the CredentialStorePlugin to allow the user to manage the credential store. CredentialManagerTool from dragom-cli-tools is such a CLI tool.

    Author:
    David Raymond
